revision.text:
{{draft}}
{{Promising draft|reason=the high amount of work put into it over a long time, see edit history}}


{{Documentation subpage}}

This template should be placed on drafts by editors other than the original draft creator to indicate that the draft has promise and is worthy of more significant review and discussion prior to deletion in order to avoid losing valuable encyclopedia content. 

== Usage ==
{{tlc|Promising draft}}
{{br}}
{{tlc|Promising draft|reason{{=}}''your reason here''}}

== Parameters ==
* {{para|reason}} – add "because ..." phrase to the message text, with the value of the param replacing the ellipsis (the word "because" is already included in the template).

==Examples==
<code><nowiki>{{Promising draft|reason=dozens of red links point to this title}}</nowiki></code>:
{{Promising draft|reason=dozens of red links point to this title}}

== Categorization ==
Such drafts are categorized within [[:Category:Promising draft articles]].  If this template is put on an article by mistake, the article will be categorized in [[:Category:Misused Promising draft template]].

== Notes ==
A [[Special:PermanentLink/848304259#Request for comment: Promising drafts|request for comment]] in June 2018 closed with a consensus that the {{tl|promising draft}} template "cannot be used to indefinitely prevent a [[WP:G13]] speedy deletion nomination".

== See also ==
*[[WP:G13 soon]]
*{{tl|Highly wanted draft}} - for drafts whose title is the target of a significant number of [[WP:RED|red links]] already in main article space.

<includeonly>{{sandbox other||
[[Category:Draft namespace templates]]
[[Category:Promising draft articles|-]]
[[Category:Talk header templates]]
[[Category:Under-construction templates]]
}}</includeonly>

